@de_Paor Yes, I hear that's what VanGogh said; in fact I'm sure I read somewhere that frustration at the difficulty in filling out forms to get gov't money was what led to the angst that caused Vincent to take his life. Unless it was his struggle with getting the art right.

@JANUSZCZAK Like most successful art forgers, Shaun Greenhalgh realised that the 'experts' at institutes, galleries, auction houses and most highfalutin dealers don't really know their subject and rely heavily on 'provenance', which is, of course, much easier to fake.

@ucylpay @MailOnline As a humble art dealer, I have to guarantee that the works I sell are genuine and would have to give a refund should it turn out otherwise. Will the much vaunted Tate experts be paying back salaries and refunding admission fees and gov't funding they have wallowed in since 1917?
@govauctionnews Yes, it's all lies! Of course I agree with you; people should work for nothing, or at least next to nothing. It's common courtesy after all.

@ThePaulLaidlaw @MailBoxesEtcUK This is disingenuous. You expect your clients to pay the price of an external shipping service which you think is too expensive! If you thought you could do it cheaper and better yourself you would, surely!

@ThePaulLaidlaw @MailBoxesEtcUK We pack and ship everything ourselves. Proper packing to prevent damage is time consuming and people who pack will insist on being paid!
